#differenrt formats for data
#txt, csv, json, xml
#txt file is a simple text file that can contain any type of data. It is a plain text format that can be easily read and edited using a text editor.
#csv file is a comma-separated values file that is used to store tabular data. It is a plain text format that uses commas to separate values. Each line in a csv file represents a row of data, and each value in the row is separated by a comma.
#json file is a JavaScript Object Notation file that is used to store data in a structured format. It is a lightweight data-interchange format that is easy for humans to read and write, and easy for machines to parse and generate. JSON files use key-value pairs to represent data, and can contain nested objects and arrays.
#xml file is an Extensible Markup Language file that is used to store data in a structured format. It is a markup language that uses tags to define elements and attributes to describe the data. XML files can be used to represent complex data structures and can be easily parsed and manipulated using various programming languages.

